Usages:
  MAIL [SEND] <passwd+-<FLAGS>> <tonick> <toname@host> <valid time> <msg>
  MAIL [LS|CAT|COUNT] <passwd+-FLAGS> <tonick>) <toname@host> <time> <id>
  MAIL [RM] <password+-<FLAGS>> <tonick> <toname@host> <time> <id>
  MAIL [FLAG] <pwd+-<FLG>> <tonick> <toname@host> +-<FLAGS> <id>
-  MAIL [SENT] [NAME|COUNT]
*  MAIL [SENT] [NAME|COUNT|USERS] <f.nick> <f.name@host> <time> [RM|RMAI]
-  MAIL [WHOWAS] <nick> <name@host> <time1> <time2>
*  MAIL [WHOWAS] <nick> <name@host> <time1> <time2> [RM|RMS]
-  MAIL [STATS] [MSM|MSW|MUM|MUW|MST|MSF|USED]
*  MAIL [STATS] [MSM|MSW|MUM|MUW|MST|MSF|USED|RESET] <value>
*  MAIL [SAVE]
  MAIL [HELP] <option>

  The MAIL systems allows you to send "mail" messages to irc
  users which they will get if and when they next sign on to irc.
  If they are on irc already, they'll get the mail immediately.

